{
  "id": "EA0031",
  "text": "Alan Jones. D.O.B. 30/08/1973\n\nDiagnosis: Juvenile Myoclonic Epilepsy\n\nMedication: Epilim 1.5 g in the morning and 1g at night\nClobazam 10 mg once-a-day\n\nInvestigations: MRI normal\nEEG (2010) generalised spike and wave activity with photosensitivity\n\nMr Jones’s epilepsy is well controlled on the above dose of epilim without any significant side-effects. He did have a breakthrough seizure recently but this was provoked by sleep deprivation. He continues to get occasional myoclonic jerks but these are not troublesome. I would therefore recommend continuing on the same dose of medication\n\nI have arranged a follow-up in nurse specialist clinic.\n\n",
